        <h2 id="max-width" tabindex="-1">
          Max-width <a class="anchor-link" href="#max-width"> </a>
        </h2>
        <div class="heading-children">
          <div>
            <p>Max-width defines the maximum width of the content of a page.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p>
              Note that some sections such as&nbsp;<code>Body start</code
              >&nbsp;and&nbsp;<code>Body end</code>&nbsp;use a fluid design for
              background colour and styling, but content such as text, links and
              icons are restricted within the max-width limit.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p>The default maximum width is&nbsp;<code>1200px</code>.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <h2 id="responsive-breakpoint" tabindex="-1">
          Responsive breakpoint
          <a class="anchor-link" href="#responsive-breakpoint"> </a>
        </h2>
        <p>
          Breakpoint is the width that determines how your responsive layout
          behaves across devices. The default breakpoint is <code>â‰¥768px</code>.
        </p>
        <h2 id="page-templates" tabindex="-1">
          Page templates <a class="anchor-link" href="#page-templates"> </a>
        </h2>
        <p>
          All pages must use the following structure inside the
          <code>&lt;body&gt;</code> tag. The page width is on the
          <a href="#max-width">max-width</a> limit. Note the <code>id</code> tag
          is for reference and can be
        </p>
        <div class="table-responsive">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Section Name</th>
                <th>HTML Tag</th>
                <th>Description</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>Body start</td>
                <td>
                  <code
                    >&lt;section class="govcy-container-fluid"
                    id="bodyStartContainer"&gt; &lt;/section&gt;</code
                  >
                </td>
                <td>
                  To be used to render the content before
                  the&nbsp;<code>&lt;header&gt;</code>&nbsp;such as
                  <mark>skip link</mark> and <mark>cookie consent</mark> (Skip
                  link must always be first). Width must be fluid, same as the
                  viewport.
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Header</td>
                <td>
                  <code
                    >&lt;header class="govcy-header" id="headerContainer"&gt;
                    &lt;/header&gt;</code
                  >
                </td>
                <td>
                  To be used as the page&nbsp;<mark>header</mark>. Width must be
                  fluid, same as the viewport.
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Before main</td>
                <td>
                  <code
                    >&lt;section class="govcy-container"
                    id="beforeMainContainer"&gt; &lt;/section&gt;</code
                  >
                </td>
                <td>
                  To be used to render the content before
                  the&nbsp;<code>&lt;main&gt;</code>&nbsp;(i.e.&nbsp;<mark
                    >back link</mark
                  >&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;<mark>breadcrumbs</mark>&nbsp;only ) . Must
                  comply with the&nbsp;<mark>max-width</mark>&nbsp;reference
                  above and be placed in the center of the viewport.
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Main</td>
                <td>
                  <code
                    >&lt;main class="govcy-container" id="mainContainer"&gt;
                    &lt;/main&gt;</code
                  >
                </td>
                <td>
                  To be used to render the service/website content
                  (i.e.&nbsp;<mark>question page</mark>). Must comply with
                  the&nbsp;<mark>max-width</mark>&nbsp;reference above and be
                  placed in the center of the viewport. This section can have
                  one of the layouts described in the&nbsp;<mark
                    >layout section</mark
                  >.
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Footer</td>
                <td>
                  <code
                    >&lt;footer class="govcy-footer" id="footerContainer"&gt;
                    &lt;/footer&gt;</code
                  >
                </td>
                <td>
                  To be used as the page&nbsp;<mark>footer</mark>. Width must be
                  fluid, same as the viewport
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Body end</td>
                <td>
                  <code
                    >&lt;section class="govcy-container-fluid"
                    id="bodyEndContainer"&gt; &lt;/section&gt;</code
                  >
                </td>
                <td>
                  To be used to render the content after
                  the&nbsp;<code>&lt;footer&gt;</code>. Width must be fluid,
                  same as the viewport.
                </td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
